{"heading":"Baptism is in similitude of the death, burial, and resurrection of Christ—The wages of sin is death—Christ brings eternal life.","number":6,"verseCount":23,"verses":[[1,["What shall we say then? Shall we continue in sin, that ",["grace",["study-note-ref","a",[["D&C 20:32 (29–34)","dc-testament/dc/20.32"],"."]]]," may abound?"]],[2,[["God forbid",["study-note-ref","a",["GR May it not be!"]]],". How shall we, that are dead to ",["sin",["study-note-ref","b",[["Mosiah 2:41","bofm/mosiah/2.41"],"."]]],", live any longer therein?"]],[3,["Know ye not, that so many of us as were ",["baptized",["study-note-ref","a",[["Mosiah 27:25","bofm/mosiah/27.25"],"."]]]," into Jesus Christ were baptized into his death?"]],[4,["Therefore we are ",["buried",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Baptism, Immersion","tg/baptism-immersion"],"."]]]," with him by ",["baptism",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Baptism","tg/baptism"],"."]]]," into death: that like as Christ was raised up from the ",["dead",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Jesus Christ, Death of","tg/jesus-christ-death-of"],"."]]]," by the glory of the Father, even so we also should ",["walk",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Walking with God","tg/walking-with-god"],"."]]]," in ",["newness",["study-note-ref","e",[["TG Baptism, Qualifications for","tg/baptism-qualifications-for"],"; ",["Man, New, Spiritually Reborn","tg/man-new-spiritually-reborn"],"."]]]," of life."]],[5,["For if we have been planted together in the ",["likeness",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Jesus Christ, Types of, in Memory","tg/jesus-christ-types-of-in-memory"],"."]]]," of his ",["death",["study-note-ref","b",[["Col. 2:20","nt/col/2.20"],"; ",["3:3","nt/col/3.3"],"; ",["2 Tim. 2:11","nt/2-tim/2.11"],"."]]],", we shall be also ",["in the likeness",["clarity-word"]]," of ",["his",["clarity-word"]]," ",["resurrection",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Resurrection","tg/resurrection"],"."]]],":"]],[6,["Knowing this, that our ",["old",["study-note-ref","a",[["Eph. 4:22 (22–24)","nt/eph/